The paper deals with privacy preserving data publishing, which is a topic that falls under the database (cs.DB) and cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-categories. The proposed algorithm involves statistical techniques, which are commonly used in machine learning and data mining (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the worst-case scenario, which involves analyzing the distribution of sensitive values, a topic that falls under the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves information theory (cs.IT) in proving that the anonymized datasets protect individual privacy.
